theorem Topology.iterate_closure_interior_stabilizes
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    ∀ n : ℕ,
      ((fun S : Set X => closure (interior S))^[n + 2]) A =
        closure (interior A) := by
  intro n
  induction n with
  | zero =>
      -- Two iterations already stabilise by idempotence.
      simpa using
        (Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
          (X := X) (A := A))
  | succ n ih =>
      -- Rewrite the `(n + 3)`-rd iterate as one more application.
      have h₁ :
          ((fun S : Set X => closure (interior S))^[n + 3]) A =
            ((fun S : Set X => closure (interior S))^[n + 2])
              (closure (interior A)) := by
        simpa [Nat.succ_add, Nat.add_comm, Nat.add_assoc] using
          (Function.iterate_succ_apply'
            (fun S : Set X => closure (interior S)) (n + 2) A)
      -- The operator fixes `closure (interior A)` after any number of iterations.
      have h₂ :
          ((fun S : Set X => closure (interior S))^[n + 2])
              (closure (interior A)) = closure (interior A) := by
        simpa using
          (Topology.iterate_closure_interior_fixed
            (X := X) (A := A) (n := n + 2))
      simpa [h₂, Nat.succ_add, Nat.add_comm, Nat.add_assoc] using h₁

theorem Topology.closure_inter_interior_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    (closure A ∩ interior A : Set X) = interior A := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    exact hx.2
  · intro hxInt
    have hxA : x ∈ A := interior_subset hxInt
    have hxCl : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
    exact And.intro hxCl hxInt
